Art can be such, that one occasionally feels one can interact intimately with it, or even fall right into it.One American artist is now sharing that experience by showcasing some of his extraordinary 3D works in a travelling exhibition in Cape Town.Michigan-born Kurt Wenner developed his love of art at a very young age. Today he is one the world's most highly acclaimed artists.Usually known for painting his unique creations on sidewalks and landmark locations across the world, you may now see it all under one roof.The Incredible Illusions exhibition is unique in that it IS totally interactive - there are no "do not touch" signs anywhere.* For more on this, join Tanya Nefdt in her interactive experience in the gallery above.eNCA